snippet.textDisplay: Wow...some people assume it's just one writer, writing everything.  I can tell the difference between Riley's work, James' work, Alex's work, Colin, and especially Jon. Just like you can tell if Woody Allen wrote the script, all his actors eventually start sounding like him.  Probably since James works with Riley the most...his own presentational style (qv his stand up) does a symbiotic dance with Riley's writing.  It's like watching a great dancer pair do a fox trot.  Where as when Riley does his own material...it's like Cossacks jumping off their heels, imbued with Frenetic Energy.  Linus tries to deliver Riley's material with the same enthusiasm, often times waiting for the rimshot and confetti...and letting the Gruyere linger in the air.  It's always interesting to see them try out new talent or snag Yvonne when they don't have anyone left in the building, but really...tech news without Riley or James is just like trying to carry on a conversation with Ursula from Mad About You.  It may be oddly funny, but leaves one frustrated when the punchlines don't land...and it's the delivery not the writing.
